  <!-- X noteheads (<notehead>x</notehead>): dead/muted notes. The notation part draws a cross
       notehead; the tab part draws "X" in place of the fret on the matching string. Notation pitch
       and tab string are independent, so they need not correspond.
       - M1: quarters, notation pitch held at B4 (no ledger lines), tab <string> varies 6/4/2/1 so
         each X lands on the right line.
       - M2: beamed eighths (notation pitch/string held) so the beam is the only new thing.
       - M3: a whole-note chord (three stacked X noteheads / three stacked tab X's).
       - M4: a realistic mix — a normal note (G4 / tab fret 0) beamed with an X-notehead dyad
         (A3+D4 / tab strings 2+1), the way dead-note strums appear in real scores. The X notes
         carry real pitches just like normal notes; the notehead only changes the glyph. -->
  <part id="P1">
